====Alternate forms====
*[[ヤ]] (''ya'') - katakana


===Particle===
[[Category:Japanese particles]]
'''や''' (''ya'')

#[[and]]
#: Used to conjoin nouns, や (''ya'') implies that the list is not limited to the nouns named. Contrast with [[と]] (''to''), the other particle typically used to conjoin nouns, which implies that the list is limited to the stated nouns.
#* お[[年寄り]]'''や'''体の不自由な方は登録[[する|しません]]か。
#*:お[[としより]]'''や'''からだのふじゆうなかたはとうろく[[する|しません]]か。
#*:''O-[[toshiyori]] '''ya''' karada no fujiyū na kata wa tōroku [[suru|shimasen]] ka.''
#*:[[don’t|Don’t]] [[senior]]s '''and''' the physically handicapped '''[and others]''' register?

===Verb===
[[Category:Japanese Type 3 Verbs]]
'''や''' (''ya'')

# (''regional'') [[is]], [[are]]
#: Variation on the Japanese [[copula]] だ (''da''), associated with the [[w:Kansai|Kansai region]] and particularly [[w:Osaka|Osaka]]. The use of や (''ya'') is common in fictional dialogue attributed to characters from Osaka.
#: [[やん]] (''yan'') is the negative form of や (''ya'').
#*[[まあ]]、[[ぼちぼち]]'''や'''[[な|なあ]]。
#*:''Maa, bochibochi '''ya''' naa.''
#*:Well, things '''are''' slow.'' (''A stereotypical Osaka expression'')

